{"title_page": "Bandar Malaysia Utara MRT station", "text_new": "{{Infobox station\n| name = {{KLRT color code2|SSP|21}}<br>Bandar Malaysia North\n| symbol_location = my\n| symbol = mrt\n| type = [[rapid transit|MRT station]]\n| logo = \n| logo_size = \n| image = \n| image_size = \n| image_caption = \n| address = [[Bandar Malaysia]], [[Kuala Lumpur]], [[Malaysia]].\n| line ={{rint|my|12}} {{KLRT lines|12}}\n| other = \n| platform = Island\n| tracks = 2\n| parking = Available, pay.\n| bicycle = \n| baggage_check = \n| passengers = \n| pass_year = \n| pass_percent = \n| pass_system = \n| status = Under construction\n| opened = \n| rebuilt = \n| electrified = \n| ADA = \n| code = {{KLRT color code2|SSP|21}}\n| owned = [[MRT Corp]]\n| zone = \n| services = {{s-rail|title=Klang Valley MRT}}\n{{s-line|system=Klang Valley MRT|line=Sungai Buloh-Serdang-Putrajaya Line|previous=Chan Sow Lin|next=Bandar Malaysia South}}\n| mpassengers = \n}}\nThe '''Bandar Malaysia North MRT station''' is a [[Rapid transit|Mass Rapid Transit]] (MRT) [[underground station]] under construction that will serve the future suburb of [[Bandar Malaysia]] in [[Kuala Lumpur]], [[Malaysia]]. It will be one of the stations on [[Klang Valley Mass Rapid Transit]] (KVMRT) [[Sungai Buloh-Serdang-Putrajaya Line]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mymrt.com.my/en/ssp/project-info/route-map|title=MYMRT {{!}} MRT Corp - Official webpage for the Klang Valley My Rapid Transit.|website=www.mymrt.com.my|language=en|access-date=2017-05-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170627024608/http://mymrt.com.my/en/ssp/project-info/route-map|archive-date=2017-06-27|url-status=dead}}</ref> The station will be built at the site of [[Simpang Airport]], along with [[Bandar Malaysia South station]] and the rest of the Bandar Malaysia development.\n\nThe Bandar Malaysia North MRT station expected to complete and start operation on 2022.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://mrt.com.my/ssp/Bandar_Malaysia_North_Station.htm Bandar Malaysia North MRT Station | mrt.com.my]\n* [http://www.mymrt.com.my Klang Valley Mass Rapid Transit]\n* [http://www.mymrt.com.my/hawk-eye-view/ MRT Hawk-Eye View]\n\n{{Klang Valley train stations|state=collapsed}}\n\n{{coord missing|Malaysia}}\n\n[[Category:Railway stations in Kuala Lumpur]]\n[[Category:Rapid transit stations in Kuala Lumpur]]\n[[Category:Sungai Buloh-Serdang-Putrajaya Line]]\n\n{{Malaysia-railstation-stub}}\n{{metro-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox station\n| name = {{KLRT color code2|SSP|21}}<br>Bandar Malaysia North\n| symbol_location = my\n| symbol = mrt\n| type = [[rapid transit|MRT station]]\n| logo = \n| logo_size = \n| image = \n| image_size = \n| image_caption = \n| address = [[Bandar Malaysia]], [[Kuala Lumpur]], [[Malaysia]].\n| line ={{rint|my|12}} {{KLRT lines|12}}\n| other = \n| platform = Island\n| tracks = 2\n| parking = Available, pay.\n| bicycle = \n| baggage_check = \n| passengers = \n| pass_year = \n| pass_percent = \n| pass_system = \n| status = Under construction\n| opened = \n| rebuilt = \n| electrified = \n| ADA = \n| code = {{KLRT color code2|SSP|21}}\n| owned = [[MRT Corp]]\n| zone = \n| services = {{s-rail|title=Klang Valley MRT}}\n{{s-line|system=Klang Valley MRT|line=Sungai Buloh-Serdang-Putrajaya Line|previous=Chan Sow Lin|next=Bandar Malaysia South}}\n| mpassengers = \n}}\nThe '''Bandar Malaysia North MRT station''' is a [[Rapid transit|Mass Rapid Transit]] (MRT) [[underground station]] under construction that will serve the future suburb of [[Bandar Malaysia]] in [[Kuala Lumpur]], [[Malaysia]]. It will be one of the stations on [[Klang Valley Mass Rapid Transit]] (KVMRT) [[Sungai Buloh-Serdang-Putrajaya Line]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mymrt.com.my/en/ssp/project-info/route-map|title=MYMRT {{!}} MRT Corp - Official webpage for the Klang Valley My Rapid Transit.|website=www.mymrt.com.my|language=en|access-date=2017-05-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170627024608/http://mymrt.com.my/en/ssp/project-info/route-map|archive-date=2017-06-27|url-status=dead}}</ref>. The station will be built at the site of [[Simpang Airport]], along with [[Bandar Malaysia South station]] and the rest of the Bandar Malaysia development.\n\nThe Bandar Malaysia North MRT station expected to complete and start operation on 2022.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://mrt.com.my/ssp/Bandar_Malaysia_North_Station.htm Bandar Malaysia North MRT Station | mrt.com.my]\n* [http://www.mymrt.com.my Klang Valley Mass Rapid Transit]\n* [http://www.mymrt.com.my/hawk-eye-view/ MRT Hawk-Eye View]\n\n{{Klang Valley train stations|state=collapsed}}\n\n{{coord missing|Malaysia}}\n\n[[Category:Railway stations in Kuala Lumpur]]\n[[Category:Rapid transit stations in Kuala Lumpur]]\n[[Category:Sungai Buloh-Serdang-Putrajaya Line]]\n\n{{Malaysia-railstation-stub}}\n{{metro-stub}}\n", "name_user": "DannyS712", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fixing the location of periods / full stops", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bandar_Malaysia_Utara_MRT_station"}
{"title_page": "CCR4-Not", "text_new": "'''C'''arbon '''C'''atabolite '''R'''epression - '''N'''egative '''O'''n '''T'''ATA-less, or '''CCR4-Not''', is a [[multiprotein complex]] that functions in gene expression.<ref name=\"Collart pp. 438\u2013454\">{{cite journal | last=Collart | first=Martine A. | title=The Ccr4-Not complex is a key regulator of eukaryotic gene expression | journal=Wiley Interdisciplinary Reviews: RNA | publisher=Wiley | volume=7 | issue=4 | date=2016-01-29 | issn=1757-7004 | doi=10.1002/wrna.1332 | pages=438\u2013454| pmid=26821858 | pmc=5066686 }}</ref><ref name=\"Miller Reese pp. 315\u2013333\">{{cite journal | last=Miller | first=Jason E. | last2=Reese | first2=Joseph C. | title=Ccr4-Not complex: the control freak of eukaryotic cells | journal=Critical Reviews in Biochemistry and Molecular Biology | publisher=Informa UK Limited | volume=47 | issue=4 | date=2012-03-15 | issn=1040-9238 | doi=10.3109/10409238.2012.667214 | pages=315\u2013333| pmid=22416820 | pmc=3376659 }}</ref> The complex has multiple enzymatic activies as both a [[Polyadenylation|poly(A)]] 3'-5' [[exonuclease]] and a [[ubiquitin ligase]].<ref name=\"Aslam Mittal Koch Andrau 2009 pp. 3840\u20133850\">{{cite journal | last=Aslam | first=Akhmed | last2=Mittal | first2=Saloni | last3=Koch | first3=Frederic | last4=Andrau | first4=Jean-Christophe | last5=Winkler | first5=G. Sebastiaan | editor-last=Wickens | editor-first=Marvin | title=The Ccr4\u2013Not Deadenylase Subunits CNOT7 and CNOT8 Have Overlapping Roles and Modulate Cell Proliferation | journal=Molecular Biology of the Cell | publisher=American Society for Cell Biology (ASCB) | volume=20 | issue=17 | year=2009 | issn=1059-1524 | doi=10.1091/mbc.e09-02-0146 | pages=3840\u20133850}}</ref><ref name=\"pmid11889047\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Chen J, Chiang YC, Denis CL | title = CCR4, a 3'-5' poly(A) RNA and ssDNA exonuclease, is the catalytic component of the cytoplasmic deadenylase | journal = EMBO J | volume = 21 | issue = 6 | pages = 1414\u201326 |date=Mar 2002 | pmid = 11889047 | pmc = 125924 | doi = 10.1093/emboj/21.6.1414 }}</ref><ref name=\"entrez\">{{cite web | title = Entrez Gene: CNOT6 CCR4-NOT transcription complex, subunit 6| url = https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/entrez?Db=gene&Cmd=ShowDetailView&TermToSearch=57472| accessdate = }}</ref><ref name=\"Albert Hanzawa Legtenberg de Ruwe pp. 355\u2013364\">{{cite journal | last=Albert | first=Thomas K. | last2=Hanzawa | first2=Hiroyuki | last3=Legtenberg | first3=Yvonne I.A. | last4=de Ruwe | first4=Marjolein J. | last5=van den Heuvel | first5=Fiona A.J. | last6=Collart | first6=Martine A. | last7=Boelens | first7=Rolf | last8=Timmers | first8=H.Th.Marc | title=Identification of a ubiquitin-protein ligase subunit within the CCR4-NOT transcription repressor complex | journal=The EMBO Journal | publisher=Wiley | volume=21 | issue=3 | date=2002-02-01 | issn=0261-4189 | doi=10.1093/emboj/21.3.355 | pages=355\u2013364}}</ref> The complex is present both in the [[Cell nucleus|nucleus]] where it regulates transcription and in the [[cytoplasm]] where it associates with translating ribosomes and [[Post-transcriptional modification|RNA processing]] bodies.<ref name=\"Collart pp. 438\u2013454\">{{cite journal | last=Collart | first=Martine A. | title=The Ccr4-Not complex is a key regulator of eukaryotic gene expression | journal=Wiley Interdisciplinary Reviews: RNA | publisher=Wiley | volume=7 | issue=4 | date=2016-01-29 | issn=1757-7004 | doi=10.1002/wrna.1332 | pages=438\u2013454| pmid=26821858 | pmc=5066686 }}</ref><ref name=\"Miller Reese pp. 315\u2013333\">{{cite journal | last=Miller | first=Jason E. | last2=Reese | first2=Joseph C. | title=Ccr4-Not complex: the control freak of eukaryotic cells | journal=Critical Reviews in Biochemistry and Molecular Biology | publisher=Informa UK Limited | volume=47 | issue=4 | date=2012-03-15 | issn=1040-9238 | doi=10.3109/10409238.2012.667214 | pages=315\u2013333| pmid=22416820 | pmc=3376659 }}</ref> \n\n== Subunits ==\nThe human CCR4-Not complex is composed of structural (non-catalytic) subunits and those that have [[exonucleases|exonuclease]] and [[Ubiquitin ligase|E3 ligase]] activity. Some but not all of the human subunits are conserved in [[Saccharomyces cerevisiae|budding yeast]].<ref name=\"Albert pp. 809\u2013817\">{{cite journal | last=Albert | first=T. K. | title=Isolation and characterization of human orthologs of yeast CCR4-NOT complex subunits | journal=Nucleic Acids Research | publisher=Oxford University Press (OUP) | volume=28 | issue=3 | date=2000-02-01 | issn=1362-4962 | doi=10.1093/nar/28.3.809 | pages=809\u2013817}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Subunit !! MW (kDa){{ref label|rounding|A|A}} !! Key Features\n|-\n| [[CNOT1|CNOT1]] || 267 || \"Scaffold\" with non-catalytic function. Linked to the maintenance of [[embryonic stem cell|embryonic stem cells]].<ref name=\"Zheng Dumitru Lackford Freudenberg pp. 910\u2013922\">{{cite journal | last=Zheng | first=Xiaofeng | last2=Dumitru | first2=Raluca | last3=Lackford | first3=Brad L. | last4=Freudenberg | first4=Johannes M. | last5=Singh | first5=Ajeet P. | last6=Archer | first6=Trevor K. | last7=Jothi | first7=Raja | last8=Hu | first8=Guang | title=Cnot1, Cnot2, and Cnot3 Maintain Mouse and Human ESC Identity and Inhibit Extraembryonic Differentiation | journal=STEM CELLS | publisher=Wiley | volume=30 | issue=5 | date=2012-04-09 | issn=1066-5099 | doi=10.1002/stem.1070 | pages=910\u2013922}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[CNOT2|CNOT2]] || 60 || Structural component. Linked to the maintenance of [[embryonic stem cell|embryonic stem cells]].<ref name=\"Zheng Dumitru Lackford Freudenberg pp. 910\u2013922\">{{cite journal | last=Zheng | first=Xiaofeng | last2=Dumitru | first2=Raluca | last3=Lackford | first3=Brad L. | last4=Freudenberg | first4=Johannes M. | last5=Singh | first5=Ajeet P. | last6=Archer | first6=Trevor K. | last7=Jothi | first7=Raja | last8=Hu | first8=Guang | title=Cnot1, Cnot2, and Cnot3 Maintain Mouse and Human ESC Identity and Inhibit Extraembryonic Differentiation | journal=STEM CELLS | publisher=Wiley | volume=30 | issue=5 | date=2012-04-09 | issn=1066-5099 | doi=10.1002/stem.1070 | pages=910\u2013922}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[CNOT3|CNOT3]] || 82 || Structural component. Linked to the maintenance of [[embryonic stem cell|embryonic stem cells]].<ref name=\"Hu Kim Xu Leng pp. 837\u2013848\">{{cite journal | last=Hu | first=G. | last2=Kim | first2=J. | last3=Xu | first3=Q. | last4=Leng | first4=Y. | last5=Orkin | first5=S. H. | last6=Elledge | first6=S. J. | title=A genome-wide RNAi screen identifies a new transcriptional module required for self-renewal | journal=Genes & Development | publisher=Cold Spring Harbor Laboratory | volume=23 | issue=7 | date=2009-04-01 | issn=0890-9369 | doi=10.1101/gad.1769609 | pages=837\u2013848}}</ref><ref name=\"Zheng Dumitru Lackford Freudenberg pp. 910\u2013922\">{{cite journal | last=Zheng | first=Xiaofeng | last2=Dumitru | first2=Raluca | last3=Lackford | first3=Brad L. | last4=Freudenberg | first4=Johannes M. | last5=Singh | first5=Ajeet P. | last6=Archer | first6=Trevor K. | last7=Jothi | first7=Raja | last8=Hu | first8=Guang | title=Cnot1, Cnot2, and Cnot3 Maintain Mouse and Human ESC Identity and Inhibit Extraembryonic Differentiation | journal=STEM CELLS | publisher=Wiley | volume=30 | issue=5 | date=2012-04-09 | issn=1066-5099 | doi=10.1002/stem.1070 | pages=910\u2013922}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[CNOT4|CNOT4]] || 64 || Active as E3 [[ubiquitin]] ligase.<ref name=\"Albert Hanzawa Legtenberg de Ruwe pp. 355\u2013364\">{{cite journal | last=Albert | first=Thomas K. | last2=Hanzawa | first2=Hiroyuki | last3=Legtenberg | first3=Yvonne I.A. | last4=de Ruwe | first4=Marjolein J. | last5=van den Heuvel | first5=Fiona A.J. | last6=Collart | first6=Martine A. | last7=Boelens | first7=Rolf | last8=Timmers | first8=H.Th.Marc | title=Identification of a ubiquitin-protein ligase subunit within the CCR4-NOT transcription repressor complex | journal=The EMBO Journal | publisher=Wiley | volume=21 | issue=3 | date=2002-02-01 | issn=0261-4189 | doi=10.1093/emboj/21.3.355 | pages=355\u2013364}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[CNOT6|CNOT6]] || 63 || 3'-5' [[exonuclease]] with preference for [[Polyadenylation|polyadenylated]] mRNA substates.<ref name=\"pmid11889047\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Chen J, Chiang YC, Denis CL | title = CCR4, a 3'-5' poly(A) RNA and ssDNA exonuclease, is the catalytic component of the cytoplasmic deadenylase | journal = EMBO J | volume = 21 | issue = 6 | pages = 1414\u201326 |date=Mar 2002 | pmid = 11889047 | pmc = 125924 | doi = 10.1093/emboj/21.6.1414 }}</ref><ref name=\"entrez\">{{cite web | title = Entrez Gene: CNOT6 CCR4-NOT transcription complex, subunit 6| url = https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/entrez?Db=gene&Cmd=ShowDetailView&TermToSearch=57472| accessdate = }}</ref> Has a human paralog [[CNOT6L]].\n|-\n| [[CNOT7|CNOT7]] || 33 || 3'-5' [[exonuclease]] that is partially redundant with CNOT7. <ref name=\"Aslam Mittal Koch Andrau 2009 pp. 3840\u20133850\">{{cite journal | last=Aslam | first=Akhmed | last2=Mittal | first2=Saloni | last3=Koch | first3=Frederic | last4=Andrau | first4=Jean-Christophe | last5=Winkler | first5=G. Sebastiaan | editor-last=Wickens | editor-first=Marvin | title=The Ccr4\u2013Not Deadenylase Subunits CNOT7 and CNOT8 Have Overlapping Roles and Modulate Cell Proliferation | journal=Molecular Biology of the Cell | publisher=American Society for Cell Biology (ASCB) | volume=20 | issue=17 | year=2009 | issn=1059-1524 | doi=10.1091/mbc.e09-02-0146 | pages=3840\u20133850}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[CNOT8|CNOT8]] || 34 || 3'-5' [[exonuclease]]. <ref name=\"Aslam Mittal Koch Andrau 2009 pp. 3840\u20133850\">{{cite journal | last=Aslam | first=Akhmed | last2=Mittal | first2=Saloni | last3=Koch | first3=Frederic | last4=Andrau | first4=Jean-Christophe | last5=Winkler | first5=G. Sebastiaan | editor-last=Wickens | editor-first=Marvin | title=The Ccr4\u2013Not Deadenylase Subunits CNOT7 and CNOT8 Have Overlapping Roles and Modulate Cell Proliferation | journal=Molecular Biology of the Cell | publisher=American Society for Cell Biology (ASCB) | volume=20 | issue=17 | year=2009 | issn=1059-1524 | doi=10.1091/mbc.e09-02-0146 | pages=3840\u20133850}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[CNOT9|CNOT9]] || 34 || Serves a non-catalytic function.<ref name=\"Pavanello Hall Airhihen Winkler pp. 3437\u20133450\">{{cite journal | last=Pavanello | first=Lorenzo | last2=Hall | first2=Benjamin | last3=Airhihen | first3=Blessing | last4=Winkler | first4=Gerlof Sebastiaan | title=The central region of CNOT1 and CNOT9 stimulates deadenylation by the Ccr4\u2013Not nuclease module | journal=Biochemical Journal | publisher=Portland Press Ltd. | volume=475 | issue=21 | date=2018-11-09 | issn=0264-6021 | doi=10.1042/bcj20180456 | pages=3437\u20133450}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[CNOT10|CNOT10]] || 82 || Non-catalytic subunit that forms a module with CNOT11 that is absent in fungi.<ref name=\"Mauxion Pr\u00e8ve S\u00e9raphin 2013 pp. 267\u2013276\">{{cite journal | last=Mauxion | first=Fabienne | last2=Pr\u00e8ve | first2=Brigitte | last3=S\u00e9raphin | first3=Bertrand | title=C2ORF29/CNOT11 and CNOT10 form a new module of the CCR4-NOT complex | journal=RNA Biology | publisher=Informa UK Limited | volume=10 | issue=2 | year=2013 | issn=1547-6286 | doi=10.4161/rna.23065 | pages=267\u2013276}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[CNOT11|CNOT11]] || 55 || Non-catalytic subunit that forms a module with CNOT10 that is absent in fungi.<ref name=\"Mauxion Pr\u00e8ve S\u00e9raphin 2013 pp. 267\u2013276\">{{cite journal | last=Mauxion | first=Fabienne | last2=Pr\u00e8ve | first2=Brigitte | last3=S\u00e9raphin | first3=Bertrand | title=C2ORF29/CNOT11 and CNOT10 form a new module of the CCR4-NOT complex | journal=RNA Biology | publisher=Informa UK Limited | volume=10 | issue=2 | year=2013 | issn=1547-6286 | doi=10.4161/rna.23065 | pages=267\u2013276}}</ref>\n|}\n{{note label|rounding|A|A}}Molecular weight of human subunits from Uniprot.\n\n== See also ==\n*[[Gene expression]]\n\n== References ==\n<!--- See http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Footnotes on how to create references using<ref></ref> tags, these references will then appear here automatically -->\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{MolBioGeneExp}}\n{{Portal bar|Biology|border=no}}\n\n<!--- Categories --->\n[[Category:Molecular biology]]\n[[Category:Gene expression]]\n[[Category:Protein complexes]]\n[[Category:RNA-binding proteins]]\n", "text_old": "'''C'''arbon '''C'''atabolite '''R'''epression - '''N'''egative '''O'''n '''T'''ATA-less, or '''CCR4-Not''', is a [[multiprotein complex]] that functions in gene expression.<ref name=\"Collart pp. 438\u2013454\">{{cite journal | last=Collart | first=Martine A. | title=The Ccr4-Not complex is a key regulator of eukaryotic gene expression | journal=Wiley Interdisciplinary Reviews: RNA | publisher=Wiley | volume=7 | issue=4 | date=2016-01-29 | issn=1757-7004 | doi=10.1002/wrna.1332 | pages=438\u2013454| pmid=26821858 | pmc=5066686 }}</ref><ref name=\"Miller Reese pp. 315\u2013333\">{{cite journal | last=Miller | first=Jason E. | last2=Reese | first2=Joseph C. | title=Ccr4-Not complex: the control freak of eukaryotic cells | journal=Critical Reviews in Biochemistry and Molecular Biology | publisher=Informa UK Limited | volume=47 | issue=4 | date=2012-03-15 | issn=1040-9238 | doi=10.3109/10409238.2012.667214 | pages=315\u2013333| pmid=22416820 | pmc=3376659 }}</ref> The complex has multiple enzymatic activies as both a [[Polyadenylation|poly(A)]] 3'-5' [[exonuclease]] and a [[ubiquitin ligase]].<ref name=\"Aslam Mittal Koch Andrau 2009 pp. 3840\u20133850\">{{cite journal | last=Aslam | first=Akhmed | last2=Mittal | first2=Saloni | last3=Koch | first3=Frederic | last4=Andrau | first4=Jean-Christophe | last5=Winkler | first5=G. Sebastiaan | editor-last=Wickens | editor-first=Marvin | title=The Ccr4\u2013Not Deadenylase Subunits CNOT7 and CNOT8 Have Overlapping Roles and Modulate Cell Proliferation | journal=Molecular Biology of the Cell | publisher=American Society for Cell Biology (ASCB) | volume=20 | issue=17 | year=2009 | issn=1059-1524 | doi=10.1091/mbc.e09-02-0146 | pages=3840\u20133850}}</ref><ref name=\"pmid11889047\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Chen J, Chiang YC, Denis CL | title = CCR4, a 3'-5' poly(A) RNA and ssDNA exonuclease, is the catalytic component of the cytoplasmic deadenylase | journal = EMBO J | volume = 21 | issue = 6 | pages = 1414\u201326 |date=Mar 2002 | pmid = 11889047 | pmc = 125924 | doi = 10.1093/emboj/21.6.1414 }}</ref><ref name=\"entrez\">{{cite web | title = Entrez Gene: CNOT6 CCR4-NOT transcription complex, subunit 6| url = https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/entrez?Db=gene&Cmd=ShowDetailView&TermToSearch=57472| accessdate = }}</ref><ref name=\"Albert Hanzawa Legtenberg de Ruwe pp. 355\u2013364\">{{cite journal | last=Albert | first=Thomas K. | last2=Hanzawa | first2=Hiroyuki | last3=Legtenberg | first3=Yvonne I.A. | last4=de Ruwe | first4=Marjolein J. | last5=van den Heuvel | first5=Fiona A.J. | last6=Collart | first6=Martine A. | last7=Boelens | first7=Rolf | last8=Timmers | first8=H.Th.Marc | title=Identification of a ubiquitin-protein ligase subunit within the CCR4-NOT transcription repressor complex | journal=The EMBO Journal | publisher=Wiley | volume=21 | issue=3 | date=2002-02-01 | issn=0261-4189 | doi=10.1093/emboj/21.3.355 | pages=355\u2013364}}</ref> The complex is present both in the [[Cell nucleus|nucleus]] where it regulates transcription and in the [[cytoplasm]] where it associates with translating ribosomes and [[Post-transcriptional modification|RNA processing]] bodies.<ref name=\"Collart pp. 438\u2013454\">{{cite journal | last=Collart | first=Martine A. | title=The Ccr4-Not complex is a key regulator of eukaryotic gene expression | journal=Wiley Interdisciplinary Reviews: RNA | publisher=Wiley | volume=7 | issue=4 | date=2016-01-29 | issn=1757-7004 | doi=10.1002/wrna.1332 | pages=438\u2013454| pmid=26821858 | pmc=5066686 }}</ref><ref name=\"Miller Reese pp. 315\u2013333\">{{cite journal | last=Miller | first=Jason E. | last2=Reese | first2=Joseph C. | title=Ccr4-Not complex: the control freak of eukaryotic cells | journal=Critical Reviews in Biochemistry and Molecular Biology | publisher=Informa UK Limited | volume=47 | issue=4 | date=2012-03-15 | issn=1040-9238 | doi=10.3109/10409238.2012.667214 | pages=315\u2013333| pmid=22416820 | pmc=3376659 }}</ref> \n\n== Subunits ==\nThe human CCR4-Not complex is composed of structural (non-catalytic) subunits and those that have [[exonucleases|exonuclease]] and [[Ubiquitin ligase|E3 ligase]] activity. Some but not all of the human subunits are conserved in [[Saccharomyces cerevisiae|budding yeast]].<ref name=\"Albert pp. 809\u2013817\">{{cite journal | last=Albert | first=T. K. | title=Isolation and characterization of human orthologs of yeast CCR4-NOT complex subunits | journal=Nucleic Acids Research | publisher=Oxford University Press (OUP) | volume=28 | issue=3 | date=2000-02-01 | issn=1362-4962 | doi=10.1093/nar/28.3.809 | pages=809\u2013817}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Subunit !! MW (kDa){{ref label|rounding|A|A}} !! Key Features\n|-\n| [[CNOT1|CNOT1]] || 267 || Structural component. Linked to the maintenance of [[embryonic stem cell|embryonic stem cells]].<ref name=\"Zheng Dumitru Lackford Freudenberg pp. 910\u2013922\">{{cite journal | last=Zheng | first=Xiaofeng | last2=Dumitru | first2=Raluca | last3=Lackford | first3=Brad L. | last4=Freudenberg | first4=Johannes M. | last5=Singh | first5=Ajeet P. | last6=Archer | first6=Trevor K. | last7=Jothi | first7=Raja | last8=Hu | first8=Guang | title=Cnot1, Cnot2, and Cnot3 Maintain Mouse and Human ESC Identity and Inhibit Extraembryonic Differentiation | journal=STEM CELLS | publisher=Wiley | volume=30 | issue=5 | date=2012-04-09 | issn=1066-5099 | doi=10.1002/stem.1070 | pages=910\u2013922}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[CNOT2|CNOT2]] || 60 || Structural component. Linked to the maintenance of [[embryonic stem cell|embryonic stem cells]].<ref name=\"Zheng Dumitru Lackford Freudenberg pp. 910\u2013922\">{{cite journal | last=Zheng | first=Xiaofeng | last2=Dumitru | first2=Raluca | last3=Lackford | first3=Brad L. | last4=Freudenberg | first4=Johannes M. | last5=Singh | first5=Ajeet P. | last6=Archer | first6=Trevor K. | last7=Jothi | first7=Raja | last8=Hu | first8=Guang | title=Cnot1, Cnot2, and Cnot3 Maintain Mouse and Human ESC Identity and Inhibit Extraembryonic Differentiation | journal=STEM CELLS | publisher=Wiley | volume=30 | issue=5 | date=2012-04-09 | issn=1066-5099 | doi=10.1002/stem.1070 | pages=910\u2013922}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[CNOT3|CNOT3]] || 82 || Structural component. Linked to the maintenance of [[embryonic stem cell|embryonic stem cells]].<ref name=\"Hu Kim Xu Leng pp. 837\u2013848\">{{cite journal | last=Hu | first=G. | last2=Kim | first2=J. | last3=Xu | first3=Q. | last4=Leng | first4=Y. | last5=Orkin | first5=S. H. | last6=Elledge | first6=S. J. | title=A genome-wide RNAi screen identifies a new transcriptional module required for self-renewal | journal=Genes & Development | publisher=Cold Spring Harbor Laboratory | volume=23 | issue=7 | date=2009-04-01 | issn=0890-9369 | doi=10.1101/gad.1769609 | pages=837\u2013848}}</ref><ref name=\"Zheng Dumitru Lackford Freudenberg pp. 910\u2013922\">{{cite journal | last=Zheng | first=Xiaofeng | last2=Dumitru | first2=Raluca | last3=Lackford | first3=Brad L. | last4=Freudenberg | first4=Johannes M. | last5=Singh | first5=Ajeet P. | last6=Archer | first6=Trevor K. | last7=Jothi | first7=Raja | last8=Hu | first8=Guang | title=Cnot1, Cnot2, and Cnot3 Maintain Mouse and Human ESC Identity and Inhibit Extraembryonic Differentiation | journal=STEM CELLS | publisher=Wiley | volume=30 | issue=5 | date=2012-04-09 | issn=1066-5099 | doi=10.1002/stem.1070 | pages=910\u2013922}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[CNOT4|CNOT4]] || 64 || Active as E3 [[ubiquitin]] ligase.<ref name=\"Albert Hanzawa Legtenberg de Ruwe pp. 355\u2013364\">{{cite journal | last=Albert | first=Thomas K. | last2=Hanzawa | first2=Hiroyuki | last3=Legtenberg | first3=Yvonne I.A. | last4=de Ruwe | first4=Marjolein J. | last5=van den Heuvel | first5=Fiona A.J. | last6=Collart | first6=Martine A. | last7=Boelens | first7=Rolf | last8=Timmers | first8=H.Th.Marc | title=Identification of a ubiquitin-protein ligase subunit within the CCR4-NOT transcription repressor complex | journal=The EMBO Journal | publisher=Wiley | volume=21 | issue=3 | date=2002-02-01 | issn=0261-4189 | doi=10.1093/emboj/21.3.355 | pages=355\u2013364}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[CNOT6|CNOT6]] || 63 || 3'-5' [[exonuclease]] with preference for [[Polyadenylation|polyadenylated]] mRNA substates.<ref name=\"pmid11889047\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Chen J, Chiang YC, Denis CL | title = CCR4, a 3'-5' poly(A) RNA and ssDNA exonuclease, is the catalytic component of the cytoplasmic deadenylase | journal = EMBO J | volume = 21 | issue = 6 | pages = 1414\u201326 |date=Mar 2002 | pmid = 11889047 | pmc = 125924 | doi = 10.1093/emboj/21.6.1414 }}</ref><ref name=\"entrez\">{{cite web | title = Entrez Gene: CNOT6 CCR4-NOT transcription complex, subunit 6| url = https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/entrez?Db=gene&Cmd=ShowDetailView&TermToSearch=57472| accessdate = }}</ref> Has a human paralog [[CNOT6L]].\n|-\n| [[CNOT7|CNOT7]] || 33 || 3'-5' [[exonuclease]] that is partially redundant with CNOT7. <ref name=\"Aslam Mittal Koch Andrau 2009 pp. 3840\u20133850\">{{cite journal | last=Aslam | first=Akhmed | last2=Mittal | first2=Saloni | last3=Koch | first3=Frederic | last4=Andrau | first4=Jean-Christophe | last5=Winkler | first5=G. Sebastiaan | editor-last=Wickens | editor-first=Marvin | title=The Ccr4\u2013Not Deadenylase Subunits CNOT7 and CNOT8 Have Overlapping Roles and Modulate Cell Proliferation | journal=Molecular Biology of the Cell | publisher=American Society for Cell Biology (ASCB) | volume=20 | issue=17 | year=2009 | issn=1059-1524 | doi=10.1091/mbc.e09-02-0146 | pages